es explicitly)\nAudio:\n  日本語音声のみ → Japanese Audio Only\n  英語吹替あり / 英語版 → English Dub Available\n  韓国語吹替 → Korean Dub\n\nSubtitle:\n  日本語字幕のみ → Japanese Subtitles Only\n  英語字幕あり → English Subtitles\n  英語字幕なし / 字幕なし → No English Subtitles\n  多言語字幕 → Multilingual Subtitles\n  韓国語字幕 / 中国語字幕 → Korean / Chinese Subtitles\n\nRegion (媒体別に正しく対応):\n  DVD の場合:\n    リージョン2 / 国内版 / 日本版 (DVD) → Region 2 Japan / NTSC-J\n    リージョン1 (DVD) → Region 1 (US/Canada)\n    リージョン3 (DVD) → Region 3 Asia\n  Blu-ray の場合:\n    リージョンA / 国内版 / 日本版 (Blu-ray) → Region A Japan\n    リージョンB → Region B (Europe/Africa/Oceania)\n    リージョンC → Region C (China/South Asia)\n  共通:\n    リージョンフリー / 全リージョン対応 → Region Free\n    NTSC-J → NTSC-J (Japan)\n\nEdition:\n  日本版 / 国内向け → Japanese Edition\n  北米版 / 米国版 → US Edition\n  アジア版 → Asia Edition\n  韓国版 → Korean Edition\n  台湾版 → Taiwan Edition\n  香港版 → Hong Kong Edition\n  中国版 → China Edition\n  輸入版 / インポート → Import Edition\n\nTITLE\n- HARD LIMIT: 80 chars maximum. eBay rejects titles exceeding 80 chars.\n- GOAL: Maximize SEO discoverability by packing every source-verified fact within the 80-char budget.\n  Unused characters = lost search visibility. Compete globally with US/EU collectors.\n- TRUTH BOUND: Only include facts derivable from source. Fabricated keywords (RARE/LIMITED/VINTAGE\n  without source confirmation) violate Rule 2 and risk account suspension.\n- Shorter title acceptable when source provides limited information. Lying is worse than being short.\n- SEO KEYWORD ORDER (front-load highest-value terms first — Franchise+Character within first 30 chars):\n  1. Franchise/Series (Frieren / Jujutsu Kaisen / Demon Slayer / One Piece / Evangelion)\n  2. Character name (Frieren / Gojo / Tanjiro / Luffy / Rei Ayanami)\n  3. Item type / Format (Acrylic Stand / Shikishi / Original Cel / Tapestry / Blu-ray Box Set)\n  4. Studio / Manufacturer (if stated and space allows)\n  5. Edition / variant (if source confirms — Limited Edition / Ichiban Kuji / Event Exclusive)\n  6. Package status if space allows (Sealed / No Box)\n- Allowed symbols: & / : - . , and apostrophe \' for possessives (e.g., Frieren\'s, Sailor Moon\'s)\n- Forbidden symbols: " ( ) [ ]\n- Do NOT include: shipping promises, seller opinions, condition adjectives, language about returns.\n- Example titles:\n  Frieren: Beyond Journey\'s End Frieren Acrylic Stand Sealed Japan\n  Jujutsu Kaisen Satoru Gojo Original Cel Wit Studio Animation Art\n  Demon Slayer Tanjiro Kamado Shikishi Art Board Signed Event\n  One Piece Monkey D. Luffy Tapestry Wall Scroll B2 Japan\n  Neon Genesis Evangelion Rei Ayanami Original Production Cel Setup\n  Attack on Titan Complete Series Blu-ray Box Set Limited Edition Japan\n\nDESCRIPTION\n- English ASCII only, <= 480 chars, single natural paragraph.\n- FIRST SENTENCE: Must contain Franchise + Character + Item type (primary search keywords).\n  Example: This Frieren: Beyond Journey\'s End Frieren acrylic stand is from the Japanese anime series.\n  Example: This original production cel from Neon Genesis Evangelion features Rei Ayanami.\n  Example: This Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba Blu-ray Limited Edition Box Set is from Japan.\n- Include naturally: Franchise / Character / Studio (if stated) / Item type / Format / Edition info /\n  Region code (if stated) / Audio language (if stated) / Year (if stated) / Package status\n- If box or case included: state condition separately from item condition.\n- DEFECT REPORTING (CRITICAL): If source mentions ANY defect from DEFECT MAPPING, include it in Description.\n  Use EN translations from DEFECT MAPPING for accurate terminology.\n- BOUNDARY NOTE: If item is manga, doujinshi, trading card, figure, or video game, note:\n  "[Use Manga / Trading Card / Figure / Game specific prompt]"\n- Exclude: shipping terms, seller opinions, return policies, purchase history.\n\nPRODUCTNAME\n- Format: [Franchise] [Character] [Item Type], English ASCII only\n- Include studio or manufacturer if stated and clearly identified from source\n- Examples:\n  Frieren: Beyond Journey\'s End Frieren Acrylic Stand\n  Jujutsu Kaisen Satoru Gojo Original Cel Wit Studio\n  Demon Slayer Tanjiro Kamado Shikishi\n  Attack on Titan Complete Series Blu-ray Limited Edition\n  Spy x Family Anya Forger Rubber Strap Keychain\n  Sailor Moon Usagi Tsukino Original Production Cel Setup\n\nCATEGORY\nSelect ONE numeric eBay ID from CATEGORY ROUTING section above.\nIf item is out of scope (manga / TCG / figure / game), output: N/A\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT (exactly):\nTitle: ...\nDescription: ...\nProductName: ...\nCategory: ...\n\nCRITICAL: Never output a "Condition:" line.\nCRITICAL: Never output an "EbayCategory:" line.\n\nVERIFICATION (must pass before returning):\n1. Title is 80 chars or under HARD LIMIT.\n2. Description <= 480 chars.\n3. Only ASCII letters/numbers/spaces and allowed symbols (& / : - . , and apostrophe \' for possessives) used throughout.\n4. No CJK characters or emoji anywhere in output.\n5. Title front-loads Franchise/Series within the first 30 chars.\n6. Description first sentence contains Franchise + Character + Item type keywords.\n7. CATEGORY field uses one of the 6 valid eBay numeric IDs (1529 / 617 / 261063 / 261057 / 261051 / 69528) or N/A.\n8. Condition/status words appear only if explicitly stated in source.\n9. No forbidden symbols in Title (no " ( ) [ ]). Apostrophe \' allowed for possessives.\n10. If source mentions any defect (箱なし/箱傷み/欠品/塗装ムラ/破損・割れ/ジャンク/傷/色褪せ/糊残り/焼け/シミ/折れ/印刷ムラ/角スレ/セル劣化/反り/カビ etc.), Description MUST include it.\n11. Every spec in output has a corresponding source in the Japanese text. If not found in source, do NOT include.\n12. If source explicitly confirms bootleg/KO/replica/unofficial: output Cannot-list 4-line format. Never output Bootleg / KO / Knock-off / Replica / Counterfeit / Fake / Unofficial / Unlicensed / Authentic (as standalone) / Official (as standalone authenticity claim) unless source confirms.\n13. ANTIQUE only if source confirms 100+ years old