rap Not Included\n  ピックアップカバー欠品 → Pickup Cover Missing\n\nMISSING ACCESSORIES DETECTION\nIf source contains ANY of the following, include in Description:\n  元箱なし / ケースなし → "Original case not included"\n  アームなし / トレモロアーム欠品 → "Tremolo arm not included"\n  説明書なし → "Manual not included"\n  ストラップなし → "Strap not included"\n\nCONDITION TERMS (3 systems — use terms appropriate to item type)\nOperational / Electronics (動作状態):\n  Tested-Working (動作確認済)\n  Sound-Tested (音出し確認済)\n  Pickup OK (ピックアップ動作OK)\n  Output OK (出力確認済)\n  Untested (動作未確認)\n  For Parts (ジャンク / 部品取り)\n  Non-functional (動作不可)\n  Pot Noise / Pot Crackle (ポット異音)\n  Jack Issue / Jack Damage (ジャック故障)\n  Switch Issue / Switch Crackle (スイッチ不良)\n\nPlayability / Setup (プレイアビリティ状態 — include when source states):\n  Action Good (弦高良好)\n  Fret Wear Present (フレット摩耗あり)\n  Fret Buzz (ビビりあり)\n  Truss Rod Adjustable (トラスロッド余裕あり)\n  Truss Rod Maxed Out (トラスロッド余裕なし)\n  High Action (弦高高め)\n  Neck Bow (ネック順反り) / Back-Bow (逆反り)\n  Intonation Issue (音程ずれ)\n\nCosmetic / Structural (外観状態):\n  Mint (傷なし / 未使用品同等)\n  Excellent (ごく軽微な使用感のみ)\n  Very Good (VG) (軽い傷・使用感あり)\n  Good (使用感・傷あり、機能問題なし)\n  Fair (傷・汚れ目立つ)\n  Poor (状態不良)\n\nVintage-specific expressions (source-confirmed only):\n  with provenance documents (ソース「書類付き」「証明書付き」明記時のみ)\n  all-original (ソース「オールオリジナル / all original」明記時のみ)\n  matching original parts (ソース明記時のみ)\n  FORBIDDEN: authenticated / verified / guaranteed / authentic [Make/Era] — AI cannot certify provenance\n\nTCG TERMS PROHIBITED: NM / LP / MP / HP / DMG are TCG-specific grading terms.\nDo NOT use these terms in guitar, bass, ukulele, or mandolin listings. Use Cosmetic condition terms above.\n\nPOWER SPECIFICATION (active electronics only — most acoustic and passive guitars do not need this section)\nActive pickup instruments (guitars with EMG / Fishman Aura / onboard preamp):\n  9V Battery: 9V × 1 (most active pickups — EMG / Bartolini)\n  9V Battery × 2: some dual-battery active systems\n  18V: some Ibanez / Fishman Acoustic preamp systems\nNote: Passive electric guitars (no onboard preamp) → No power section. Acoustic-electric with passive pickup → No power section.\n\nLANGUAGE / COUNTRY OF ORIGIN\nCountry of Origin (include in Title when stated — SEO priority after Brand/Model/Type):\n  MIJ / Made in Japan → Title priority (high demand from international buyers)\n  CIJ / Crafted in Japan → Title priority\n  MIA / Made in USA → Title priority\n  MIM / Made in Mexico → Title priority\n  MII / Made in Indonesia → Title priority (when source states)\n  MIC / Made in China → Title priority (when source states)\n  MIK / Made in Korea → Title priority (when source states)\n  MIV / Made in Vietnam → Title priority (when source states)\n\nLanguage notes (include in Description when stated):\n  日本語マニュアル付き → "Japanese Owner\'s Manual included"\n  教則DVD / 教則本付き → "Japanese Instruction Book/DVD included"\n\nBRAND UNKNOWN RULE\nIf source does not identify brand:\n  Do NOT invent a brand name. Do NOT guess based on visual appearance or style.\n  In Title: use guitar type + key specs only (e.g., "Acoustic Guitar Spruce Top Japan Vintage 1980s")\n  In ProductName: use "Unbranded" only when eBay brand field requires an entry\n  In Description: state "Brand not identified from source."\n\nTITLE\n- HARD LIMIT: 80 chars maximum. eBay rejects titles exceeding 80 chars.\n- GOAL: Maximize SEO discoverability by packing every source-verified fact within the 80-char budget.\n  Unused characters = lost search visibility. Compete globally with guitar collectors and musicians worldwide.\n- TRUTH BOUND: Only include facts derivable from source. Fabricated keywords (RARE / VINTAGE / PRE-CBS\n  without source confirmation) violate Rule 2 and risk eBay VeRO account suspension.\n- Shorter title acceptable when source provides limited information. Lying is worse than being short.\n- SEO KEYWORD ORDER (front-load highest-value terms — Brand + Model + Type within first 30 chars):\n  1. Brand name (Fender / Gibson / Martin / Tokai / Ibanez / Yamaha)\n  2. Model name/number — copy EXACTLY from source (Stratocaster not Strat, Les Paul not LP, RG550 not RG 550)\n  3. Instrument type (Electric Guitar / Acoustic Guitar / Bass Guitar / Ukulele)\n  4. Country of Origin when stated (MIJ / MIA / MIM / Made in Japan / Made in USA)\n  5. Year / decade if stated (1980s / 1957 / Pre-CBS / Showa)\n  6. Color / Finish if notable (Sunburst / Natural / Black / Olympic White / Cherry)\n  7. Condition note if critical (For Parts / Untested)\n- Allowed symbols: & / : - . , and apostrophe \' for possessives (e.g., D\'Angelico, D\'Addario)\n- Forbidden symbols: " ( ) [ ]\n- Example titles:\n  Fender Japan Stratocaster MIJ Electric Guitar 1980s Sunburst Tested\n  Gibson Les Paul Standard Electric Guitar Made in USA 1990s Heritage Cherry\n  Martin D-28 Acoustic Guitar Made in USA Rosewood Natural Excellent\n  Tokai Love Rock Electric Guitar MIJ Vintage 1982 Sunburst Les Paul-style\n  Ibanez RG550 Electric Guitar Japan 1987 Road Flare Red Floyd Rose\n  Yamaha FG800 Dreadnought Acoustic Guitar Natural Solid Spruce Top\n\nDESCRIPTION\n- English ASCII only, <= 480 chars, single natural paragraph.\n- FIRST SENTENCE: Must contain Brand + Model + Instrument type (primary search keywords).\n  Example: "This Fender Japan Stratocaster MIJ electric guitar is a 1980s solid-body instrument with an alder body."\n  Example: "This Gibson Les Paul Standard electric guitar is a Made in USA model from the 1990s."\n  Example: "This Tokai Love Rock electric guitar is a Made in Japan vintage model from 1982."\n- Include naturally: Brand / Model / Instrument type / Body material / Fretboard material /\n  Pickup type / Bridge type / String count / Color / Serial number / Year / Country of origin /\n  Condition terms / Defects / Accessories included\n- DEFECT REPORTING (CRITICAL): If source mentions ANY defect from DEFECT MAPPING, include in Description.\n  Use EN translations from DEFECT MAPPING for accurate terminology.\n  Omitting known defects violates eBay policy.\n- If source states Country of Origin, include in Description even if already in Title.\n- Exclude: shipping terms, seller opinions, return policies, purchase history.\n\nPRODUCTNAME\n- Format: [Brand] [Model] [Instrument Type], English ASCII only\n- Include country, year, or material if space allows\n- Examples:\n  Fender Japan Stratocaster Electric Guitar\n  Gibson Les Paul Standard Electric Guitar\n  Martin D-28 Acoustic Guitar\n  Tokai Love Rock Electric Guitar MIJ\n  Ibanez RG550 Electric Guitar Japan 1987\n\nCATEGORY\nSelect ONE numeric eBay ID from CATEGORY ROUTING section above.\nIf item is out of scope (Effects Pedal / Amplifier / Synthesizer / Japanese Instrument / Consumer Audio): N/A\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT (exactly):\nTitle: ...\nDescription: ...\nProductName: ...\nCategory: ...\n\nCRITICAL: Never output a "Condition:" line.\nCRITICAL: Never output an "EbayCategory:" line.\n\nVERIFICATION (must pass before returning):\n1. Title is 80 chars or under HARD LIMIT.\n2. Description <= 480 chars.\n3. Only ASCII letters/numbers/spaces and allowed symbols (& / : - . , and apostrophe \' for possessives) used throughout.\n4. No CJK characters or emoji anywhere in output.\n5. Title front-loads Brand + Model + Type within the first 30 chars.\n6. Description first sentence contains Brand + Instrument type keywords.\n7. CATEGORY field uses one of the 6 valid eBay numeric IDs (33034 / 33021 / 4713 / 119544 / 33036 / 33074) or N/A.\n8. Condition/status words appear only if explicitly stated in source.\n9. No forbidden symbols in Title (no " ( ) [ ]). Apostrophe \' allowed for possessives.\n10. If source mentions any defect, Description MUST include it using DEFECT MAPPING EN translations.\n11. Every spec in output has a corresponding source. If not found in source, do NOT include.\n12. If source explicitly confirms bootleg/KO/replica/unofficial: output Cannot-list 4-line format. Never output Bootleg / KO / Knock-off / Replica / Counterfeit / Fake / Unofficial / Unlicensed / Authentic (as standalone) / Official (as standalone authenticity claim) unless source confirms.\n13. MODEL NAME in Title must be copied EXACTLY from source (Stratocaster not Strat, Les Paul not LP, RG550 not RG 550).\n14. Boundary rule — if item is Effects Pedal / Amplifier / Synthesizer / Traditional Japanese Instrument / Consumer Audio: Category must be N/A and Description must include [Use appropriate prompt] note.\n\nIf any check fails, regenerate until all pass.\n\nInput: ${fullText}\n' };

