/ Benzaiten / Daikoku\nMaterials: Bronze / Gilt Bronze / Wood Carving / Dry Lacquer / Kanshitsu / Stone / Gold Leaf / Polychrome / Kirikane\nTechniques: Carved / Cast / Ichiboku / Yosegi / Kanshitsu / Hollow Dry Lacquer\nStyles: Wayo / Karayo / Tenjikuyo / Zenshuyo\nEras: Asuka / Nara / Heian / Kamakura / Muromachi / Momoyama / Edo / Meiji / Taisho / Showa\nMakers: Unkei / Kaikei / Jocho / Enku / Mokujiki / Kosho\nSects: Tendai / Shingon / Jodo / Zen / Nichiren / Shinto\nFeatures: Antique / Signed / Temple / Shrine / Original Box / Tomobako / Shofuda / Made in Japan / Handmade / Traditional\n\nPRODUCT TYPE DETECTION (Buddhist Art-specific dictionary)\n- Figures / Deities:\n  仏像 -> Buddha Statue / Buddhist Figure\n  観音 -> Kannon / Guanyin\n  如来 -> Nyorai / Tathagata\n  菩薩 -> Bosatsu / Bodhisattva\n  不動明王 -> Fudo Myoo\n  地蔵 -> Jizo\n  阿弥陀 -> Amida / Amitabha\n  大日如来 -> Dainichi Nyorai / Vairocana\n  薬師如来 -> Yakushi Nyorai / Bhaisajyaguru\n- Ritual Implements:\n  仏壇 -> Buddhist Altar (Butsudan)\n  数珠 / 念珠 -> Prayer Beads (Juzu / Mala)\n  木魚 -> Mokugyo (Wooden Fish)\n  香炉 -> Incense Burner / Censer\n  燭台 -> Candlestick\n  りん -> Rin (Singing Bowl / Bell)\n- Materials:\n  木彫 -> Wood Carving\n  銅像 / 青銅 -> Bronze\n  乾漆 -> Dry Lacquer (Kanshitsu)\n  石仏 -> Stone Buddha\n\nMATERIAL MAPPING\n- 木 / 木製 -> Wood / Wooden\n- 漆 / 乾漆 -> Lacquer / Dry Lacquer\n- 銅 / 青銅 / 真鍮 -> Copper / Bronze / Brass\n- 石 / 石製 -> Stone\n- 金 / 金箔 -> Gold / Gold Leaf\n- 銀 -> Silver\n\nTITLE (SEO Priority)\n- Language: English ASCII only.\n- Length: 40-75 chars (target 68-75, shorter OK if source-bound, NEVER exceed 75). If >75, shorten but keep SEO value.\n- Allowed symbols: & / : - . ,\n- Forbidden symbols: " \' ( ) [ ]\n- SEO order: Japanese + Deity/Implement + Material + School/Period if stated + Motif/Attributes + Antique.\n\nDESCRIPTION (SEO Priority)\n- English ASCII only, <= 480 chars, single natural paragraph.\n- FIRST SENTENCE: Include item type + material + origin (Japan).\n- Include only if explicitly stated: deity/subject, pose/attributes, temple/school, dimensions (cm and inches), weight, technique (carved, cast, lacquered), period/era, inscriptions, included items (stand, altar fittings), provenance.\n- DEFECT/ISSUE REPORTING (CRITICAL): do not omit any known defect.\n\nDEFECT KEYWORDS\n- 欠損 -> missing part\n- 破損 -> damage / breakage\n- 虫食い -> worm damage\n- 経年劣化 -> age deterioration\n- ひび / ヒビ -> crack\n- 欠け / カケ -> chip\n- 直し / 修復 -> repair / restoration\n\nPRODUCTNAME\n- Format: Japanese [Deity/Implement] [Material/Technique], English ASCII only.\n- Examples:\n  Japanese Buddha Statue Bronze Seated Figure\n  Japanese Kannon Wood Carving Standing Bodhisattva\n  Japanese Rin Singing Bowl Bronze with Cushion\n\nCATEGORY\n- Asian Antiques > Statues / Ritual Implements.\n- If unclear: Asian Antiques > Other\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT (exactly):\nTitle: ...\nDescription: ...\nProductName: ...\nCategory: ...\n\nVERIFICATION (must pass before returning)\n1. Title length 40-75 chars (target 68-75, shorter OK if source-bound).\n2. Description <= 480 chars.\n3. Only ASCII characters and allowed symbols used throughout.\n4. No CJK characters or emoji anywhere.\n5. "Japanese" appears in Title.\n6. Correct romanized or English term for deity/implement is used.\n7. Dimensions included in Description if stated (cm and inches).\n8. Material stated in Title or Description.\n9. All stated defects are included in Description.\n10. Every spec must be supported by the source text.\n\nIf any check fails, regenerate until all pass.\n\n========================================\nREMINDER: Lying is worse than being short.\n========================================\n\nInput: ${fullText}\n' };

