Brazier / Iron Fire Bowl (heating)\n銀瓶 / Ginbin — Silver Kettle (silver or silver-plated body)\n銅瓶 / Dobin — Copper Kettle / Bronze Kettle\n\n-- ORIGIN DICTIONARY --\n\n南部鉄器 / Nambu Tekki / Nambu Ironware — Iwate Prefecture: Morioka (盛岡市) and Oshu/Mizusawa (奥州市水沢); Traditional Craft (METI 1975); Regional Collective Trademark (2008); counterfeit risk HIGH\n京都 / Kyoto — home of Ryubundo / Kibundo / Kinjudo / Onishi Seiemon (Sanjo Kamaza); lost-wax technique\n高岡 / Takaoka — Toyama Prefecture; copper and iron casting; Traditional Craft; home of Hannya Kankei workshop\n山形 / Yamagata — Yamagata Prefecture; separate iron casting tradition\n大阪 / Osaka — home of Okuni workshop\n一方堂 / Ippodo — Kyoto; traditional tea kettle dealer/workshop\n\n-- DECORATION / PATTERN DICTIONARY --\n\n霰文 / Arare / Aremon — hailstone pellet pattern (PREMIUM; highest SEO value; Nambu and Kyoto)\n槌目 / Tsuchime — hammer-mark texture (HIGH value)\n阿弥陀焼 / Amidayaki — Amida surface finish\n算木目 / Sangime — log-pile band pattern\n亀甲 / Kikko — tortoiseshell hexagonal pattern\n松 / Matsu — pine motif\n桜花 / Sakura — cherry blossom motif\n富士山 / Fuji — Mount Fuji motif (HIGH eBay search value)\n山水 / Sansui — landscape motif (associated with Kibundo silver inlay)\n龍 / Ryu — dragon motif (雲龍 / Unryu = cloud dragon)\n鳳凰 / Ho-o — phoenix motif\n唐草 / Karakusa — arabesque / scrollwork\n雷文 / Raimon — thunder/meander pattern\n蜘蛛巣 / Kumoso — spider web pattern\n金象嵌 / Kin-zogan — gold inlay\n銀象嵌 / Gin-zogan — silver inlay (Kibundo signature)\n銅象嵌 / Do-zogan — copper inlay\n\n-- SHAPE DICTIONARY --\n\n丸型 / Maru-gata — round/spherical form\n平型 / Hira-gata — flat/squat form\n撫肩 / Nadeskata — sloping shoulders\n鶴首 / Tsurukubi — crane-neck (tall slender)\n棗形 / Natsume-gata — natsume/jujube oval form\n算木 / Sangi — log-pile rectangular form\n八角 / Hakkaku — octagonal\n六角 / Rokkaku — hexagonal\n真形 / Shinari — classic smooth round chagama form\n\n-- MATERIAL DICTIONARY --\n\n鋳鉄 / Cast Iron — standard tetsubin and chagama body\n砂鉄