Genuine main-studio pieces have maker\'s mark on BOTH the kettle body AND the lid interior. Lid-only mark → W4 or W5 only; body-only mark requires kanteisho for W2.\n\n========================================\nSECTION 9: DESCRIPTION DISCLOSURE\n========================================\n\n- English ASCII only, <= 480 chars, single natural paragraph.\n- FIRST SENTENCE: object type + material + function context + origin (Japan).\n- Include ONLY if source explicitly states: workshop attribution level (W1-W6), origin, dimensions (cm AND inches), weight, pattern, casting technique, era (source-stated), authentication (box, inscription, certificate), included accessories (lid, trivet, stand), function condition.\n- FUNCTION CONDITION REQUIRED: always state water boiling status if tetsubin.\n  Examples: "Tested for water boiling; no leaks detected." / "Water boiling suitability not tested." / "For display use only due to interior rust." / "Enamel-lined interior; suitable for brewing and serving only, not for direct boiling."\n- Box and authentication status must be stated: "Comes with original Tomobako." / "No box." / "Daitokuji hakogaki inscription on box." / "Expert kanteisho included."\n- DEFECT DISCLOSURE (CRITICAL — never omit any stated defect or damage).\n\n========================================\nSECTION 10: DEFECT MAPPING (source → English)\n========================================\n\n-- CRITICAL DEFECTS (must always disclose) --\n漏れ / 水漏れ — leaking / water leakage (functional failure)\n内部塗装剥離 / 銀差し剥離 — interior lining loss / silver coating flaking (affects safe use)\nひび / ヒビ / 亀裂 — crack (structural failure)\n直し / 修復 / ロウ付け / 溶接 — repair / restoration / brazing / welding (must specify location)\n\n-- HIGH PRIORITY DEFECTS --\n内部錆 — interior rust (state severity: minor surface / flaking / heavy scale)\n取手割れ / 取手破損 — handle crack / handle damage\n凹み — dent (specify location)\n鐶付破損 — kan-tsuki ring loop damage (chagama lifting ring)\n\n-- STANDARD DEFECTS --\n外部錆 / 表面錆 — exterior rust / surface patina (stable aged patina acceptable description; active rust = rust)\n蓋ぐらつき / 蓋合わせ悪い — loose lid / poor lid fit\n摘み破損 / 摘み欠け — knob damage / missing knob\n欠け / カケ — chip (spout, rim, knob)\n蓋裏錆 — lid interior rust\n錆び付き — rust bonding (parts fused by rust)\n\nPROHIBITED DESCRIPTION: Do NOT write "beautiful patina" or "lovely aged surface" for rust. Iron kettles are food-contact items. State rust factually and clearly.\n\n========================================\nSECTION 11: CONDITION TERMS + FUNCTION CONDITION\n========================================\n\n-- CONDITION TIERS (antique metalware industry standard — NOT TCG NM/LP/MP/HP/DMG) --\n\nExcellent — No defects. Minimal natural aging. All parts (body, lid, handle/knob) present and undamaged. Patina stable. Interior clean or with normal aging.\n\nVery Good — Minor surface patina or minor exterior wear. No cracks. All parts present. Lid fits. Handle firm. Interior clean to lightly aged.\n\nGood — Visible surface patina / minor exterior rust (stable). All parts present with minor defects (small chip, slight lid wobble). Fully functional or ceremony-worthy.\n\nFair — Significant patina or exterior rust. Minor structural issues (repaired area, loose handle, chips). Past repair disclosed. May require cleaning.\n\nPoor — Major defects: large crack, active leaking, missing parts, heavy interior rust flaking, lining loss. Decorative use only. Describe specific defects in full.\n\nFor Parts / As-Is — Non-functional. Crack, heavy leaking, major structural failure. State all known defects.\n\n-- FUNCTION CONDITION (REQUIRED for all tetsubin / ginbin / dobin) --\n\nState ONE of the following in Description:\n- usable for boiling water; tested; no leaks\n- water boiling not tested; suitability unknown; use at own risk\n- not suitable for boiling; decorative use only (specify reason: interior rust / crack / lining loss / leaking)\n- enamel-lined interior; brewing and serving only; not for direct heat boiling\n- tea ceremony use only (chagama)\n\n-- MATERIAL-SPECIFIC NOTES --\n\nIron (鉄): Interior rust is common in antique tetsubin; state severity clearly\nSilver (銀): Check for dents and seam integrity\nCopper/Bronze (銅/青銅): Verdigris patina normal; structural cracking at seams is critical\nMixed materials: State each component\'s condition separately if defects differ\n\n-- ERA CONDITION CORRELATION --\n\nAntique (pre-1925): Excellent condition exceptional; Fair/Good typical for functional pieces\nVintage (1912-1945): Very Good achievable; Good common\nShowa/Heisei (post-1945): Excellent/Very Good expected for signed modern pieces\n\n========================================\nSECTION 12: BOOTLEG MUST\n========================================\n\nThe following 12 terms are ABSOLUTELY PROHIBITED in Title and Description under any circumstance:\n\nBootleg / KO / Knock-off / Counterfeit / Fake / Unofficial / Unlicensed / Authentic (standalone) / Official (standalone) / Pirate / Unauthorized / Replica (standalone)\n\nIron kettle specific additional prohibitions:\n- fake Ryubundo / forged Ryubundo mark / counterfeit 龍文堂 — using these terms to describe an item implies seller is listing a known fake; do not generate such listings\n- false origin Nambu — applying Nambu Tekki to non-Iwate production\n- fake Daitokuji hakogaki on chagama — forged inscription\n- reproduction sold as antique original (偽銘の古作品)\n- Replica standalone in Title (e.g., "Ryubundo Replica Tetsubin" — BOOTLEG MUST)\n\nFor any item triggering BOOTLEG MUST: output CANNOT_LIST and stop.\n\nVERIFICATION of BOOTLEG MUST (self-check):\nSection 12 terms: Bootleg / KO / Knock-off / Counterfeit / Fake / Unofficial / Unlicensed / Authentic (standalone) / Official (standalone) / Pirate / Unauthorized / Replica (standalone)\nThis list must match BOOTLEG MUST section exactly — diff=0.\n\n========================================\nSECTION 13: OUTPUT FORMAT + VERIFICATION\n========================================