ace\nVery Good — minor surface abrasion only; no structural lacquer loss\nGood — small lacquer skip or hairline crack; structurally sound and functional\nFair — lacquer repair visible, or significant abrasion; still usable\nFor Display — significant lacquer peeling or maki-e loss; display only\nFor Parts — broken lid, structural failure, non-functional\n\nWood (木工 — applies to 棚 wood / 茶箱 wood / 茶杓筒 wood):\nExcellent — no warpage, no crack, clean grain, smooth finish\nVery Good — minor natural patina; no structural issue\nGood — small crack or minor warp; functional\nFair — restored or significant crack; usable with care\nFor Display — significant damage; display only\nFor Parts — structural failure\n\nMetal (金物 — applies to 建水 / 蓋置 metal / 五徳 / 灰器 / 風炉 copper or bronze):\nExcellent — no corrosion; clean surface; all functions intact\nVery Good — minor natural patina only\nGood — spot rust or minor patina; functional\nFair — localized rust; usable\nFor Display — heavy rust or corrosion throughout\nFor Parts — non-functional or missing essential component\n\nFabric (布 — applies to 仕覆 / 古帛紗 / 服紗 / 出帛紗):\nExcellent — no stain, no fraying, vibrant color\nVery Good — minor age-related softening; no visible damage\nGood — small stain or minor fade; usable\nFair — restoration or significant stain; usable with condition note\nFor Display — significant fade or fraying; display only\nFor Parts — torn or severely damaged\n\nBamboo (竹 — applies to 茶杓 / 茶筅 / 柄杓):\nExcellent — no crack, no split, flexible and intact\nVery Good — minor surface split; no structural issue\nGood — small crack; functional\nFair — repaired crack; usable\nFor Display — significant crack or split; display only\nFor Parts — broken tip or structural failure\n\n========================================\nSECTION 12: BOOTLEG MUST (ABSOLUTE BAN)\n========================================\n\nNEVER use these 12 terms in Title or Description:\nBootleg / KO / Knock-off / Counterfeit / Fake / Unofficial / Unlicensed 