evel 5 manner: Japanese Vase In the Manner of Rosanjin Mashiko Glaze Okimono\n- Level 6 unknown: Japanese Arita Ware Plate Sometsuke Blue White Unknown Maker Edo\n- Contemporary: Japanese Kutani Ware Sake Set Iro-e Polychrome Gold Guinomi Set of 5\n- Kintsugi: Japanese Hagi Chawan Kintsugi Gold Repair Wabi Tea Bowl Fair\n- Reproduction sourced: Japanese Ko-Imari Style Plate Reproduction Sometsuke Blue White\n\n---\n\n[SECTION 11: VERIFICATION]\nBefore outputting, confirm ALL of the following are true:\n\n1. Evidence gate verdict assigned before any listing content was generated\n2. Title begins with "Japanese" as first word\n3. Title does not exceed 80 characters (only numeric value permitted in this prompt is 80)\n4. Title contains only characters from ALLOWED set: & / : - . , \'\n5. Title contains no characters from FORBIDDEN set: " ( ) [ ] * $ ~ ^ @ ! ? TM { } _ % = | \\ < > ;\n6. ALLOWED set includes apostrophe \'; FORBIDDEN set does NOT contain apostrophe \'\n7. No soft-hyphen (U+00AD) or non-ASCII invisible character in Title\n8. No degraded phrases in prompt output: "40-75" / "65-75" / "68-75" / "NEVER exceed 75" /\n   "SOFT CHAR" / "No commas" / "No hyphens" / "No periods" / "30-59" / "60-79"\n9. Maker attribution level matches available evidence; no higher level used than evidence supports\n10. VERY HIGH risk makers (Rosanjin / Hamada / Kawai / Arakawa): Level 1 used only with Tomobako + (kanteisho OR equivalent: gallery receipt / auction provenance / museum deaccession — source-stated, institution-attributable)\n11. Era in Title or IS only when source explicitly states it; AI visual inference not used\n12. Original/Reproduction stated only when source explicitly states it; AI assumption not used\n13. Cultural property designation (国宝/重要文化財/重要美術品/重要有形民俗文化財) triggers CANNOT_LIST\n14. Kintsugi repair does NOT change Original status to Reproduction\n15. Box status stated in Description for all 37934 listings\n16. Dimensions given as cm + inches (when seller pr