殊切手 -> Special Issue Stamp\n- 航空切手 -> Airmail Stamp\n- ふるさと切手 -> Prefecture Stamp / Regional Stamp\n- 年賀切手 -> New Year Stamp\n- 国立公園切手 -> National Park Stamp\n- 文化人切手 -> Cultural Leaders Stamp\n- 軍事切手 -> Military Stamp\n- 切手帳 -> Stamp Booklet\n- 初日カバー / FDC -> First Day Cover / FDC\n\nSTAMP QUALITY MAPPING\n- 未使用 / 美品 -> Mint\n- 未使用美品 / MNH -> Mint Never Hinged / MNH\n- ヒンジ跡あり / MH -> Mint Hinged / MH\n- 軽いヒンジ跡 -> Mint Lightly Hinged / MLH\n- 糊なし -> Mint No Gum / MNG\n- 使用済み -> Used / Cancelled\n- 消印付き -> Postally Used\n- 満月印 / 和文印 -> CDS (Circular Date Stamp)\n- CTO -> Cancelled to Order / CTO\n\nSTAMP FORMAT MAPPING\n- シート -> Full Sheet\n- 小型シート / 小シート -> Souvenir Sheet / Miniature Sheet\n- バラ -> Single\n- ブロック -> Block\n- 田型 -> Block of 4\n- 連刷 -> Se-tenant\n- ペーン / ペイン -> Pane\n- 耳紙付き -> with Selvage / with Margin\n- 目打ちなし -> Imperforate\n- 銘版付き -> with Imprint\n\nSTAMP CERTIFICATION MAPPING\n- PSE -> PSE (Professional Stamp Experts)\n- BPA -> BPA (British Philatelic Association)\n- 鑑定書付き -> with Certificate\n- 鑑定なし -> Uncertified\n\n--- COIN SECTIONS ---\n\nCOIN TYPE MAPPING\n- 硬貨 / コイン -> Coin\n- 記念硬貨 -> Commemorative Coin\n- 古銭 -> Antique Coin\n- 紙幣 / 札 -> Banknote / Paper Money\n- メダル -> Medal\n- 記念メダル -> Commemorative Medal\n- プルーフ硬貨 -> Proof Coin\n- 小判 -> Koban / Oval Gold Coin\n- 大判 -> Oban / Large Oval Gold Coin\n- 天保通宝 -> Tempo Tsuho\n- 寛永通宝 -> Kanei Tsuho\n- 穴銭 -> Holed Coin / Cash Coin\n\nCOIN COMPOSITION MAPPING\n- 金 -> Gold\n- 銀 -> Silver\n- 銅 -> Copper\n- 青銅 -> Bronze\n- ニッケル -> Nickel\n- 白銅 -> Cupronickel\n- 真鍮 -> Brass\n- アルミ -> Aluminum\n- プラチナ -> Platinum\n- ビメタル -> Bimetallic\n\nCOIN GRADE MAPPING (Sheldon Scale)\n- 完全未使用 / MS -> Mint State / MS\n- 未使用 -> Uncirculated / UNC\n- 準未使用 / AU -> About Uncirculated / AU\n- 極美品 / XF -> Extremely Fine / XF\n- 美品 / VF -> Very Fine / VF\n- 準美品 / F-VF -> Fine-Very Fine / F-VF\n- 良品 / F -> Fine / F\n- 並品 / VG -> Very Good / VG\n- プルーフ -> Proof\n\nCOIN CERTIFICATION MAPPING\n- NGC -> NGC (Numismatic Guaranty Company)\n- PCGS -> PCGS (Professional Coin Grading Service)\n- ANACS -> ANACS\n- ICG -> ICG\n- 鑑定書付き -> with Certificate\n- スラブ入り -> Slabbed / Graded\n- 鑑定なし -> Uncertified\n\nERA MAPPING\n- 江戸時代 -> Edo Period\n- 明治 -> Meiji Era\n- 大正 -> Taisho Era\n- 昭和 -> Showa Era\n- 平成 -> Heisei Era\n- 令和 -> Reiwa Era\n- 戦前 -> Pre-War\n- 戦後 -> Post-War\n\nDENOMINATION MAPPING\n- 円 -> Yen\n- 銭 -> Sen\n- 厘 -> Rin\n- 文 -> Mon\n- 両 -> Ryo\n\nTITLE (SEO Priority)\n- Language: English ASCII only.\n- Length: 40-75 chars (target 68-75, shorter OK if source-bound, NEVER exceed 80). If >80, shorten but keep SEO value.\n- Allowed symbols: & / : - . ,\n- Forbidden symbols: " \' ( ) [ ]\n\n- SEO KEYWORD ORDER - STAMPS (front-load high-value terms):\n  1. "Japan" (within first 10 chars)\n  2. Year or Era\n  3. Stamp type (Commemorative, Definitive)\n  4. Subject/Topic (Olympics, Cherry Blossom, National Park)\n  5. Format (Full Sheet, Block of 4, Single)\n  6. Quality (MNH, Used)\n  7. Face value if notable\n  8. Bonus SEO: Rare, Vintage (Category B — source-confirmed ONLY. See Rule 2); Lot (factual if applicable)\n\n- SEO KEYWORD ORDER - COINS (front-load high-value terms):\n  1. "Japan" (within first 10 chars)\n  2. Year or Era (Meiji, Edo Period)\n  3. Denomination (100 Yen, 1 Yen)\n  4. Composition (Silver, Gold)\n  5. Coin type (Commemorative, Antique)\n  6. Grade if stated (UNC, XF, MS65)\n  7. Certification if slabbed (NGC, PCGS)\n  8. Bonus SEO: Rare, Vintage (Category B — source-confirmed ONLY. See Rule 2)\n\nDESCRIPTION (SEO Priority)\n- English ASCII only, <= 480 chars, single natural paragraph.\n- FIRST SENTENCE: Must contain country + type + key identifier.\n  STAMP example: "Japan 1964 Tokyo Olympics commemorative stamp souvenir sheet in mint never hinged condition..."\n  COIN example: "Japan Meiji era 1 yen silver dragon coin in extremely fine condition..."\n- Include searchable specs naturally:\n  * Country: Japan\n  * Type (Commemorative Stamp, Silver Coin, Banknote)\n  * Year of issue / Era\n  * Denomination / Face value\n  * Subject/Topic (for stamps)\n  * Composition / Material (for coins)\n  * Quality/Grade\n  * Certification details if graded\n  * Format (Sheet, Single, Block) for stamps\n  * Dimensions/Weight if stated\n  * Catalog number if stated (Scott, JSCA for stamps; Y# for coins)\n  * Quantity if lot\n- DEFECT/ISSUE REPORTING (CRITICAL):\n  DEFECT KEYWORDS AND TRANSLATIONS:\n    - シミ -> "stains" or "toning"\n    - ヤケ / 日焼け -> "sun damage" or "yellowing"\n    - 折れ -> "crease" or "fold"\n    - 破れ -> "tear"\n    - ヒンジ跡 -> "hinge remnant"\n    - 薄い / 目打ち欠け -> "thin" or "short perforations"\n    - 錆 / サビ -> "corrosion" or "rust"\n    - 傷 -> "scratch"\n    - 磨耗 -> "wear"\n    - 変色 -> "toning" or "discoloration"\n    - 〜できず / 〜不可 -> always means NOT possible.\n  Omitting known defects is a violation of eBay policy.\n- Avoid evaluative adjectives. Exclude shipping/seller opinions.\n\nPRODUCTNAME\n- STAMP: [Year/Era] Japan [Type] [Subject], English ASCII only.\n- COIN: Japan [Era/Year] [Denomination] [Composition] [Type], English ASCII only.\n- Examples:\n  1964 Japan Olympic Commemorative Stamp Sheet\n  Japan Meiji 1 Yen Silver Dragon Coin\n  Japan Showa 100 Yen Commemorative Coin\n  Japan 1950s Definitive Stamps Lot\n\nCATEGORY\n- Stamps (all types): Stamps\n- Coins / Antique Coins: Coins & Paper Money\n- Banknotes: Coins & Paper Money\n- Medals: Coins & Paper Money\n- If unclear: N/A\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT (exactly):\nTitle: ...\nDescription: ...\nProductName: ...\nCategory: ...\n\nVERIFICATION (must pass before returning):\n1. Title length 40-75 chars (target 68-75, shorter OK if source-bound, NEVER exceed 80).\n2. Description <= 480 chars.\n3. Only ASCII characters and allowed symbols used throughout.\n4. No CJK characters or emoji anywhere.\n5. "Japan" appears within first 10 chars of Title.\n6. Year or Era included in Title if stated in source.\n7. Product type clearly identified (Stamp vs Coin vs Banknote).\n8. Quality/Grade included if stated in source.\n9. Denomination included for coins/banknotes.\n10. Composition included for coins if stated.\n11. Condition/status words appear only if explicitly stated in source.\n12. No forbidden symbols in Title.\n13. If source mentions any defect, Description MUST include it.\n14. Every spec in the output must have a corresponding source in the Japanese text.\n\nIf any check fails, regenerate until all pass.\n\nInput: ${fullText}' };

