cceptable when source provides\n  limited information. Lying is worse than being short.\n- Allowed symbols: & / : - . , # (and \' only for possessive forms)\n- Forbidden symbols: * $ ~ ^ @ ! ? ™ ( ) [ ] { } " _ % = | \\ < > ;\n- "One Piece" and "Japanese" are high-value SEO terms — include when not redundant.\n- For graded cards (PSA/BGS/CGC/SGC): grade at the START of Title.\n\nSEO KEYWORD ORDER (front-load high-value terms):\nFor Graded Cards:\n1. Grade (PSA 10, BGS 9.5) — at START of Title\n2. Character Name (Monkey D. Luffy, Roronoa Zoro)\n3. Rarity (Manga Rare, Secret Rare, Super Rare)\n4. Set Code or Name (OP01, Romance Dawn)\n5. Language (Japanese)\n6. Game identifier (One Piece Card Game / OPCG)\n\nFor Raw (Ungraded) Cards:\n1. Character Name\n2. Rarity (Manga Rare, Secret Rare, Parallel)\n3. Set Code or Name / Card Number (OP01-001)\n4. Edition or variant (Parallel, Alternate Art) if applicable\n5. Language (Japanese)\n6. Game identifier (One Piece Card Game / OPCG)\n\nLEGITIMATE KEYWORDS (use only if present in source):\n- Manga Rare / Super Parallel — only when source states マンガレア / スーパーパラレル / ★\n- Special Rare — only when source states SP / スペシャルカード\n- Secret Rare — only when source states SEC / シークレットレア\n- Super Rare — only when source states SR / スーパーレア\n- Parallel / Alternate Art — only when source states パラレル / オルタネートアート / ALT\n- Asian English — only when source states アジア英語版 / Asia English / AE\n- Promo — only when source explicitly states promotional card (プロモ / P-NNN)\n- One Piece — always include (game identity); do not repeat as "One Piece Card One Piece"\n\nCARD NUMBER FORMAT\nOne Piece cards use code + number format:\n- Booster sets: OP01-001 (code without hyphen, then hyphen, then 3-digit number)\n- Starter Decks: ST01-001, ST12-001 format | Extra Boosters: EB01-001 format\n- Include card number in Description; use set code in Title for SEO\n\nDESCRIPTION (SEO Priority)\n- English ASCII only, <= 480 chars, single natural paragraph.\n- FIRST S