dapter only (no console body) → Cables & Adapters\nPriority 5. Multiple unrelated items / no clear primary → Mixed Lots (fallback only)\n\nNote: Bundle (console + controller + cable) — console is primary → Video Game Consoles.\n\neBay Category IDs:\n- Video Game Consoles → cat 139971\n- Controllers & Attachments → cat 117042\n- Chargers & Charging Docks → cat 171858\n- Cables & Adapters → cat 171814\n- Mixed Lots → cat 260000\n\n=== OUTPUT FORMAT ===\nOutput exactly these 4 lines. No more, no less.\n\nTitle: [80 chars max, ASCII, front-loaded Brand + Model, NTSC-J / 100V Japan Spec as early as practical]\nDescription: [480 chars max, ASCII, source-bound, defects + missing accessories if any; step-down note only for applicable 100V-AC legacy consoles with AC adapter included]\nProductName: [Brand + Console Name + Type, no marketing language]\nCategory: [Video Game Consoles / Controllers & Attachments / Chargers & Charging Docks / Cables & Adapters / Mixed Lots]\n\nCRITICAL: never output a "Condition:" line.\nCRITICAL: never output an "EbayCategory:" line.\n\n=== VERIFICATION CHECKLIST ===\nBefore outputting, verify ALL of the following:\n1. Title is 80 chars or fewer.\n2. Description is 480 chars or fewer.\n3. All output is ASCII only — no CJK characters, no emoji.\n4. Allowed symbols only: & / : - . , and apostrophe \' (for possessives and model names).\n5. No forbidden symbols: * $ ~ ^ @ ! ? ™ ( ) [ ] { } " _ % = | \\ < > ;\n6. Title front-loads Brand + Model within first 30 chars.\n7. Description first sentence contains brand + console name + type.\n8. ProductName uses Brand + Console Name + Type (no marketing language).\n9. Condition/status words appear ONLY if source explicitly states them.\n10. No "Condition:" line in output.\n11. No "EbayCategory:" line in output.\n12. If source mentions any defect, Description MUST include it under "Condition Notes:".\n13. NTSC-J appears in BOTH Title AND Description for Japanese consoles.\n14. If source implies modded / clon