egory B — CONDITIONAL ALLOWANCE (only if source contains explicit evidence):\n  RARE — Only if source explicitly states rarity (limited to N units / one of N made / rare colorway)\n  LIMITED / LIMITED EDITION — Only if source confirms (serial number / production count / limited release marker)\n  VINTAGE — Only if source confirms era (1970s / Pre-1990 / estate find / decade markers in source)\n  EXCLUSIVE — Only if source confirms exclusive distribution\n  COLLECTIBLE / COLLECTORS EDITION — Only if source marks it as such\n  MINT — Only if source describes: unused / factory sealed / all parts on runners\n\nCategory C — ALWAYS ALLOWED (factual attributes from source):\n  Brand / model name / kit number / scale / build status / battery type / drive type / country of origin, etc.\n\nRULE — SOURCE-ONLY, NO INVENTION\nYou may use Category B words ONLY if the source explicitly contains evidence.\nDO NOT: Guess / Infer from similar items / Use general knowledge / Assume from visual appearance\nIf source does not provide evidence, DO NOT include Category B word.\n\nNO REPETITION: Do not repeat any token more than once in Title.\n\nBOOTLEG MUST (VeRO risk — mandatory scan before output)\n\nVERY HIGH VeRO (8 brands — most cloned/counterfeited in RC/hobby market):\n  Tamiya / Bandai (non-Gunpla plastic kits only; Gunpla = メカプラモ prompt) / Kyosho / Kato / Tomix / Hot Wheels / Tomica / Hasegawa\n\nIP-specific HIGH — Vintage special rule (4):\n  Vintage 70s-80s Tamiya RC (Grasshopper / Hornet / Buggy Champ) — source-confirmed era only\n  Vintage Hot Wheels Redline (1968-1977) — Redline must be explicitly confirmed in source\n  Vintage Tomica Made in Japan (1970s-1980s) — MIJ label must be confirmed in source\n  Vintage Kato 鉄道 (70s-80s) — era must be confirmed in source\n  FORBIDDEN ALWAYS for all Vintage above: authenticated / verified / guaranteed / authentic [Model]\n  Source-confirmed only (Description only): with provenance / all-original / original box intact / matching date