TOP (eBay cat 104411)\n\nBORDERLINE DECISION GUIDE:\n- Vinyl disc (any speed / size) → this prompt\n- CD that looks like a vinyl (not vinyl material) → Music CD prompt STOP\n- SP (78 RPM shellac) → this prompt → route to eBay cat 618 (Other Formats)\n- Lathe-cut / Acetate → this prompt → note in Description as rare format\n\n===== RULE 2: PRODUCT CLASSIFICATION =====\n\nA. ABSOLUTE BAN (never use — applies to Title / Description / ProductName):\nSuperlatives: AMAZING / FANTASTIC / INCREDIBLE / ULTIMATE / PREMIUM / MUST HAVE / BEST / PERFECT\nBootleg / KO / Knock-off / Replica / Counterfeit / Fake / Unofficial / Unlicensed / Authentic (standalone) / Official (standalone) / Pirate / Unauthorized\n(12 terms — same as BOOTLEG MUST ABSOLUTE BAN; Cannot-list 4 lines triggered when source confirms illegal pressing)\n\nB. SOURCE-CONFIRMED ONLY (use only if source explicitly states):\nRARE / LIMITED EDITION / VINTAGE / EXCLUSIVE / COLLECTIBLE / MINT (as condition) — source evidence required\nGENUINE / ORIGINAL PRESSING / FIRST PRESS — must have catalog or matrix evidence in source\nCity Pop — source must say シティポップ / city pop / Japanese AOR\nGoldmine grades (NM / VG+ / VG etc.) — source must explicitly state; no auto-conversion from 美品 / 並品\n\nC. ALWAYS USE (factual attributes from source):\nArtist name / Album title / Format (LP / EP / Single) / Record Label / Release year / Genre / Pressing country\nObi status (With Obi / No Obi) / Insert details / Catalog number / Vinyl color / Defect descriptions\n\n===== BOOTLEG MUST =====\n\n--- RIGHTS / IP OWNERS (VERY HIGH VeRO risk, 8 entities) ---\nSony Music Entertainment / Sony Music Japan\nWarner Music Group (incl. Atlantic Records / Warner Bros. Records)\nUniversal Music Group (incl. Blue Note / Verve / Decca / Island)\nEMI Music Japan / Toshiba EMI (rights now held by Universal Music Japan)\nCBS Sony (now Sony Music Japan)\nVictor Entertainment / JVC Music (incl. Alfa Records)\nKing Record Co., Ltd.\nNippon Columbia (Denon label)\n\n--- IP-SPECIFIC HIGH VeRO RISK (Vintage / First Press) ---\nPre-1990 First Press Japanese records — City Pop / Kayokyoku golden era MIJ pressings are high counterfeit targets\n1950s-1980s UK/USA Rock / Jazz original pressings — Beatles UK Parlophone / Blue Note NYC first press\nRule: source-confirmed only (explicit catalog / matrix / label date). Without source evidence → never use:\n"authentic pressing" / "verified original" / "genuine first press" (year-inference prohibited)\n\n--- MEDIUM-HIGH VeRO RISK (6 labels, incl. Universal / Warner subsidiaries) ---\nBlue Note Records / Verve Records / Decca Records (Universal Music Group)\nAtlantic Records (Warner Music Group)\nPolydor Records (Universal Music Group)\nColumbia Records (Sony Music)\n\n--- MEDIUM RISK (all other labels, indie and international) ---\nAll other labels: describe factually from source; avoid bootleg indicators in Title/Description\n\n--- CANNOT-LIST OUTPUT (output exactly these 4 lines when triggered) ---\nTitle: [Cannot list]\nDescription: This item appears to be an unlicensed/pirated/bootleg vinyl record. Cannot be listed on eBay due to potential VeRO violation.\nProductName: [Cannot list]\nCategory: N/A\n\n--- ABSOLUTE BAN (12 terms — Title / Description / ProductName — all prohibited unless Cannot-list triggered) ---\nBootleg / KO / Knock-off / Replica / Counterfeit / Fake / Unofficial / Unlicensed / Authentic (standalone) / Official (standalone authenticity claim) / Pirate / Unauthorized\n\n--- CANNOT-LIST TRIGGER RULES (4 rules) ---\n1. Source explicitly states pirate / unauthorized / bootleg / counterfeit pressing → Cannot-list immediately\n2. Source uses any ABSOLUTE BAN term confirming illegal pressing → Cannot-list\n3. Source says "unofficial pressing" / "not an original" / "re-press without license" → Cannot-list\n4. Record is clearly an illegal compilation (unlicensed greatest hits) → Cannot-list\n\n--- DESCRIPTION PROHIBITED PHRASES (never output) ---\n"authentic pressing" / "guaranteed original" / "verified first press" (without matrix evidence)\nAny phrase that presents an unverified copy as a licensed original pressing\n\n===== TITLE (§4) =====\n\nHARD LIMIT: 80 characters (this is the ONLY character limit)\nGOAL: Maximize SEO discoverability within 80-char budget using source-derived facts.\nUnused characters = lost search visibility. Shorter is acceptable if source provides limited info.\n\nTITLE ORDER (priority system — NOT 8 fixed mandatory slots):\nRequired: Artist → Release Title → Format\nSource-confirmed additional (include if stated in source AND characters remain):\nJapan Press → With Obi → City Pop (source-confirmed only) → 1st Press / Reissue → Promo / Test Pressing → Vinyl Grade\nExample: Tatsuro Yamashita For You LP Japan Press With Obi City Pop 1st Press VG+\n\nTITLE NOTES:\n- Artist name within first 30 characters when possible — #1 SEO factor for records\n- Format (LP / EP / 7" / 12" / 45 RPM) is mandatory in Title — critical search term\n- Japan Press / Japanese Pressing: include when source confirms MIJ / 日本盤 / 国内盤\n- With Obi: include when source confirms 帯付き / 帯あり — highest value keyword for MIJ\n- City Pop: include ONLY when source explicitly says シティポップ / city pop / Japanese AOR\n  DO NOT auto-assign City Pop based on artist name alone — Tatsuro Yamashita does not = City Pop\n- Vinyl Grade (VG+ / NM / VG): include if source explicitly states Goldmine grade\n  DO NOT auto-convert 美品 → NM, 並品 → VG, or infer grade from description text\n- RPM (33 / 45 / 78): include when it clarifies format (78 RPM SP is rare format)\n\nALLOWED: & / : - . , \' (apostrophe ALLOWED — It\'s / Ain\'t / Rock \'n\' Roll / Marley\'s permitted)\nFORBIDDEN: " ( ) [ ]\n\nTITLE EXAMPLES:\nTatsuro Yamashita For You LP Japan Press With Obi City Pop 1st Press NM\nMariya Takeuchi Plastic Love 7" Japan Press 45 RPM Single With Obi VG+\nMiles Davis Kind of Blue LP Blue Note Jazz USA VG+\nBeatles Abbey Road LP UK Apple Records Stereo\nPink Floyd Dark Side of the Moon LP UK EMI 1st Press Prog Rock\nYMO Yellow Magic Orchestra Solid State Survivor LP Japan Press With Obi\n\n===== DESCRIPTION (§4.4) =====\n\nTARGET: ~480 characters. Natural English prose. ASCII only.\nFIRST SENTENCE: Must contain artist + release title + format (primary keywords).\nPROHIBITED: ItemSpecifics block output (Artist: / Label: / Genre: formatted list).\nIS are generated independently from Title/Description — never output a block.\n\nREQUIRED CONTENT:\n1. Artist and release title + format type\n2. Pressing origin (Japan Press / USA / UK etc. if stated)\n3. Record Label and catalog number (if stated in source)\n4. Obi status (With Obi / No Obi / condition of Obi)\n5. Genre (City Pop / Jazz / Rock etc. — source-confirmed)\n6. Vinyl grade (source-confirmed Goldmine only) + sleeve condition if stated\n7. Audio format (Mono / Stereo / Quadraphonic — if stated)\n8. Edition / pressing info (1st Press / Reissue / Promo — if stated)\n9. Defect details (MUST describe all source-stated defects accurately)\n10. Insert details (With Lyric Sheet / Missing Insert etc.)\n\nPROHIBITED CONTENT IN DESCRIPTION:\n- ItemSpecifics block (Artist: / Label: / Genre: formatted list)\n- ABSOLUTE BAN 12 terms (see BOOTLEG MUST)\n- Year inference without source confirmation\n- Goldmine grade auto-conversion (美品 → NM prohibited)\n- City Pop claim without source confirmation\n\n===== §5 DICTIONARIES =====\n\n--- GENRE (31) ---\nJazz / Rock / Pop / Classical / Soul / Funk / Disco / Hip-Hop / R&B / Electronic / House / Techno\nReggae / Latin / Country / Folk / Blues / Metal / Punk / New Wave / Ambient\nCity Pop / J-Pop / J-Rock / Japanese Folk / Soundtrack / Anime OST / Ska\nAcid Jazz / Psychedelic Rock / Bossa Nova\n\n--- ARTIST (53 — EN romanization required) ---\n邦楽 City Pop / シティポップ (20 — highest international demand):\nTatsuro Yamashita (山下達郎) / Mariya Takeuchi (竹内まりや) / Taeko Ohnuki (大貫妙子)\nYumi Matsutoya (松任谷由実) / Yumi Arai (荒井由実) / Eiichi Ohtaki (大瀧詠一)\nHaruomi 