ラ剥がれ / ホイル剥がれ=Holo peeling / Foil peeling\nフォイル傷 / ホイル傷=Foil scratch / Holo scratch\nセンタリング偏り=Off-centering / Miscut\nインク飛び=Print error / Ink splatter\n初期傷=Factory defect / Manufacturing imperfection (NOT "early scratch")\n色移り=Color transfer / Ink bleed\n汚れ=Dirt / Staining / Grime\n黒点=Black spot / Print artifact\n印刷ズレ=Print misalignment / Frame shift\n縦線=Vertical print line\n横線=Horizontal print line\n色あせ=Fading / Discoloration\nインク剥がれ=Ink peeling / Ink separation\nくすみ=Cloudiness / Loss of gloss / Dullness\n気泡=Bubble (under foil layer)\n裂け=Tear / Split\n穴=Hole / Perforation\n水濡れ / 水シミ=Water damage / Water stain\n箔押し不良=Hot-stamp defect / Foil stamp misprint\n\n=== CONDITION TERMS ===\n未使用/未開封/新品=New / Factory Sealed\n美品/極美品=Near Mint (NM)\n良品=Lightly Played (LP)\n傷あり/使用感あり/並品=Moderately Played (MP)\nダメージあり/状態悪い=Heavily Played (HP)\nジャンク/破損=Damaged (DMG)\nGRADED CARD GUARD: If PSA/BGS/CGC/SGC grade present, use numeric grade only. Do NOT output verbal condition term (NM/LP/etc.) for graded cards.\nDEFECT GUARD: If source states defects, use the most conservative condition grade. Condition reflects source — never upgrade.\nMINT BAN: Do NOT use "Mint" as standalone verbal condition. Use NM (Near Mint) instead.\nHOBBY TERM BAN: Do NOT use "Gem Mint", "Pack Fresh", "PST", "POOR", "FAIR" without numeric PSA/BGS/CGC/SGC grade from source.\n\n=== SEO KEYWORD ORDER ===\nInclude BOTH series title and character name when possible.\n\nFor Graded Cards (PSA/BGS/CGC/SGC):\n1. Grade (PSA 10, BGS 9.5)\n2. Character Name (Pekora, Asuna, Hatsune Miku)\n3. Rarity (SP Signed, SSP, RRR, SIR)\n4. Series Title (Hololive, Sword Art Online, Project Sekai)\n5. Language (Japanese)\n6. Game (Weiss Schwarz)\n\nFor Raw (Ungraded) Cards:\n1. Character Name (Pekora, Asuna, Hatsune Miku)\n2. Rarity (SP Signed, SSP, RRR, SIR)\n3. Series Title (Hololive, Sword Art Online, Project Sekai)\n4. Condition (NM, LP)\n5. Language (Japanese)\n6. Game (Weiss Schwarz)\n\n=== LEGITIMATE KEYWORDS ===\nUse ONLY if explicitly present in source. Do not add without source evidence.\n- SP (Signed / Hot-Stamped) — only when source states サイン / SP / 箔押し\n- SSP (Super Special Signed) — only when source states SSP / スーパースペシャル\n- SIR (Super Illustrator Rare) — only when source states SIR / スーパーイラストレーターレア\n- SEC (Secret Rare) — only when source states SEC / シークレット\n- OFR (Over Frame Rare) — only when source states OFR / オーバーフレームレア\n- RRR (Triple Rare) — only when source states RRR / トリプルレア\n- SR (Super Rare) — only when source states SR / スーパーレア\n- RR (Double Rare) — only when source states RR / ダブルレア\n- CR (Climax Rare) — only when source states CR / クライマックスレア\n- BPR / PR (Promo) — only when source states promo card\n- Signed — only when source explicitly states signed / SP / SSP / SIR card\n- English Edition — only when source explicitly states English edition\n- Japanese Edition — only when source explicitly states Japanese edition\n\n=== CATEGORY ROUTING ===\nUngraded single card -> 183454 (Individual Trading Card Games Weiss Schwarz)\nGraded single (PSA/BGS/CGC/SGC) -> 183454 (Individual Trading Card Games Weiss Schwarz)\nSP/SSP/SIR/OFR high-value single -> 183454 (Individual Trading Card Games Weiss Schwarz)\nSealed Booster Box / Booster Pack -> 183456 (Weiss Schwarz Sealed Collectible Card Game Packs)\nTrial Deck / Starter Deck (sealed) -> 183456 (Weiss Schwarz Sealed Collectible Card Game Packs)\nMixed Lot -> 183454 (Individual Trading Card Games Weiss Schwarz)\nDefault -> 183454\n\n=== TITLE ===\nHARD LIMIT: 80 (eBay system maximum — enforced by platform)\nGOAL: Maximize SEO discoverability by packing every source-derived fact (character name, rarity, series title, language, card number, grade) within the 80-char budget. Unused characters = lost search visibility.\nTRUTH BOUND: Every element in Title must derive from source. Omit if unknown. Never fabricate.\nShorter OK: A shorter title built from real source facts is better than an 80-char title padded with invented details. Lying is worse than being short.\nALLOWED SYMBOLS: & / : - . , # (and \' for possessives)\nFORBIDDEN SYMBOLS: * $ ~ ^ @ ! ? ™ ( ) [ ] { } " _ % = | \\ < > ;\n"Weiss Schwarz" and "Japanese" are high-value eBay SEO terms — include when space allows.\nFor graded cards: grade at START of title.\n\n=== DESCRIPTION ===\nEnglish ASCII only, <= 480 chars, single natural paragraph.\nFIRST SENTENCE: Must contain character name + series title.\nFor SP/SSP/SIR: MUST mention "signed" or "hot-stamped" in Description.\nInclude: character name, rarity, series title, card number, language (Japanese), grade if graded.\nPublisher: Include "Published by Bushiroad" once in Description.\nUse keyword variations: "Weiss Schwarz" "WS" "Weiß Schwarz"\nIf source states defects, include under "Condition Notes:" in Description.\nNEVER include: shipping info, seller opinions, price negotiations.\n\n=== PRODUCTNAME ===\nFormat: [Character] [Rarity] [Series Title]\nExample: Pekora SP Signed Hololive / Asuna RRR Sword Art Online / Hatsune Miku SSP Project Sekai\n\n=== OUTPUT FORMAT ===\nTitle: ...\nDescription: ...\nProductName: ...\nCategory: ...\nCardName: ...\nSetName: ...\nCardNumber: ...\nRarity: ...\nLanguage: ...\nGrade: ...\nCondition: ...\nYear: ...\n\n=== EXCLUDE FROM OUTPUT ===\n- Shipping information (発送, 送料, shipping, 宅急便, メルカリ便)\n- Seller opinions and purchase instructions\n- Storage/handling descriptions\n- Japanese hashtags that are not card, anime, or character names\n- BOX/Pack types unless item itself is a sealed product\n- Price negotiations or disclaimer text\n\n=== VERIFICATION ===\nBefore returning output, confirm all checks pass:\n1. Title <= 80 chars and uses no FORBIDDEN SYMBOLS as defined in TITLE section.\n2. Description <= 480 chars, single paragraph, ASCII only, no CJK.\n3. No fabricated facts — every claim derives from source.\n4. If graded card, grade appears at START of Title.\n5. "Published by Bushiroad" appears in Description once.\n6. Character name appears in Title.\n7. Rarity code appears in Title if found in source.\n8. If SP/SSP/SIR card, "Signed" or "Hot-Stamped" appears in Title and Description.\n9. "Japanese" appears in Title unless source explicitly confirms another language.\n10. "Weiss Schwarz" or "WS" appears in Title when space allows.\n11. No shipping info or seller opinions in output.\n12. ProductName format: [Character] [Rarity] [Series Title].\n13. No CJK characters or emoji anywhere in output.\n14. Rule 2 compliance: no Category B words without explicit source evidence.\n15. All defects from source reported in Description under "Condition Notes:".\n16. No Bootleg/KO/Replica/Fake/Counterfeit/Authentic/Official in output (ABSOLUTE BAN).\n\nIf any check fails, regenerate until all pass.\n\nInput: ${fullText}\n' };

