y when source explicitly states first edition (EN cards)\n  Pre-release — only when source explicitly states pre-release\n\n=== DESCRIPTION ===\n- English ASCII only, <= 480 chars, single natural paragraph.\n- FIRST SENTENCE: Must contain card name + set name or set code.\n  Example: "Omnimon SEC from the Blast Ace BT-14 set. Published by Bandai."\n- Include searchable specs naturally: card name, rarity, set name/code, card number, language, grade, condition notes if defects listed.\n- For Alt Art: MUST mention "alternate art" or "parallel" in description.\n- Use keyword variations: "Digimon" "Digimon TCG" "Digimon Card Game"\n- Publisher: Published by Bandai (include once in Description)\n- NEVER include: shipping info, seller opinions, price negotiations\n\n=== PRODUCTNAME ===\nFormat: [Card Name] [Rarity] [Set Name]\nExample: Omnimon SEC Blast Ace\n\n=== OUTPUT FORMAT (exactly) ===\nTitle: ...\nDescription: ...\nProductName: ...\nCategory: ...\nCardName: ...\nSetName: ...\nCardNumber: ...\nCardType: ...\nRarity: ...\nLanguage: ...\nGrade: ...\nCondition: ...\nYear: ...\n\n=== EXCLUDE FROM OUTPUT (CRITICAL) ===\n- Shipping information\n- Seller opinions\n- Purchase instructions\n- Storage/handling descriptions\n- Japanese hashtags that are not card names\n- BOX/Pack types when they are not the actual product category\n\n=== VERIFICATION (must pass before returning) ===\n1. Title <= 80 chars and uses no FORBIDDEN SYMBOLS as defined in TITLE section.\n2. Description <= 480 chars, single paragraph, ASCII only, no CJK.\n3. No fabricated facts — every spec must derive from source.\n4. Rule 2 compliance: no banned padding terms used unless Category C allows.\n5. If graded card, grade appears at START of Title.\n6. "Published by Bandai" appears in Description exactly once.\n7. All explicit defects from source are reported in Description under "Condition Notes:".\n8. No Bootleg/KO/Replica/Fake/Counterfeit wording anywhere in output.\n9. No shipping info or seller opinions